The article is a transcript of Vice President Kamala Harris' remarks during the swearing-in ceremony for members of the President's Advisory Commission on Advancing Educational Equity, Excellence, and Economic Opportunity for Hispanics. Harris commends Secretary of Education Miguel Cardona for his dedication to education and emphasizes the importance of seeing the potential in children and providing them with support. She also discusses the concept of equity and the need to address the different starting points of individuals in order to ensure equal opportunity. Harris highlights the importance of not only financial resources but also the cultural environment and the broader context in which young people are raised. She concludes by administering the oath to the members of the commission.